settings.text:
Proposition 65 requires businesses to provide warnings to Californians about significant exposures to chemicals that cause cancer, birth defects or other reproductive harm. These chemicals can be in the products that Californians purchase, in their homes or workplaces, or that are released into the environment.

By requiring that this information be provided, Proposition 65 enables Californians to make informed decisions about their exposures to these chemicals. Proposition 65 also prohibits California businesses from knowingly discharging significant amounts of listed chemicals into sources of drinking water.

Proposition 65 requires California to publish a list of chemicals known to cause cancer, birth defects or other reproductive harm. This list, which must be updated at least once a year, has grown to include approximately 900 chemicals since it was first published in 1987.

Cancer:

Big D® Pheno D+ #337 Disinfectant & Deodorant (16.5 oz Aerosol Cans) - Case of 1 | This product can expose you to chemicals including o-Phenylphenol, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

e.logical e.Mulsify Low Odor Floor Stripping Solution - 4 Gallons | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Hospeco® Citrus Phenomenal Disinfectant Spray (16.5 oz Aerosol Cans) – Case of 1 | This product can expose you to chemicals including o-Phenylphenol, which are known to the State of California to cause cancer.

Misty® Chalkboard & Whiteboard Cleaner (19 oz Aerosol Cans) - Case of 1 | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Nyco® 'E-Z 20:1' Concentrated Floor Stripper (32 oz Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Trusted Clean 'Easy Lift SC' Super Concentrated Floor Wax Stripper (32 oz Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Trusted Clean 'Extraction Care' Carpet & Upholstery Cleaner (1 Gallon Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Naphthalene, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Trusted Clean 'Knock Out' Ready-To-Use Cleaner Degreaser (32 oz Bottles) - Case of 1 | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer.

Cancer and Reproductive Harm:

Claire® Ultra Low VOC Brake Parts Cleaner (50 State Formula) - 6 Cans | This product can expose you to chemicals including Ethyl Benzene, which is known to the State of California to cause cancer, and Toluene, which is known to the State of California to cause birth defects or other reproductive harm.

CleanFreak® Traffic Lane Carpet Cleaner (1 Gallon Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Ethylene Oxide, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer, or birth defects or other reproduction harm.

Nyco® 'Low Foam Delimer' Descaler Remover (1 Gallon Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Ethylene Oxide, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer, or birth defects or other reproduction harm.

Trusted Clean 'Low Foam' Floor Degreaser (1 Gallon Bottles) - Case of | This product can expose you to chemicals including Diethanolamine, which is known to the state of California to cause cancer and 2-methoxyethanol, which is known to the state of California to cause birth defects or other reproduction harm.

Reproductive Harm:

Trusted Clean 'Klinger' Detergent Thickened Bowl Cleaner (32 oz Bottles) - Case of 1 | This product can expose you to chemicals including Methanol, which is known to the state of California to cause birth defects or other reproduction harm.

settings.heading: Maintain Your Wet/Dry Vac
settings.subheading: Never store your wet/dry vac with water still in the tank. This can promote the growth of mold and mildew, ruining the equipment. Always wipe down with a dry cloth after use and allow time to air dry. You can use an air mover or fan to help speed up the drying process.
